Variables:
   Are like boxes/containers witch can hold data for us
   we can change the data later on if we want
   we can reuse the same variables as many times as we want
   There are 8 basic/primitive data types.
   Four basic data types to store whole numbers:
   1. byte
   2. short
   3. int
   4. long

   Two basic data types to store decimal numbers:
   1. float
   2. double

   One data type to store characters:
   1. char

   One data type to store true/false:
   1. boolean

   NonPrimitives:
   1. String

